{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a250b1fd-592b-4b94-ba41-3294c29e0c54","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes, the OS automatically generates a **`.ips` crash report**. You can find it in:\n\n```\n~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n```\n\nor the system-wide location:\n\n```\n/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n```\n\nLook for a file matching your process name with a `.ips` extension (JSON format). You can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them.\n\n**Tip:** If you need to symbolicate the .NET runtime frames in the `.ips` file, let me know — I can help with that using the Apple crash symbolication workflow.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a09aec21-3ff0-4c4b-b5e8-f57e8abfa3d3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without createdump. This is a knowledge question — I don't need to search a codebase. Let me answer directly.","outputTokens":226,"requestId":"CB07:E6727:1EC800B:220A027:6A052982"},"id":"80a11b36-2351-40e8-b3c2-0bae83627c41","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:46:49.796Z","parentId":"a84b8f34-0a57-4ee9-a5f9-75dc24bc2096"}
